<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="10159521">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>Here's a nicer way using closures</p>
<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$your_data</span>, function(<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>)
{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">strcmp</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;name, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;name);
});
</code></pre>
<p>Please note this is not in PHP's documentation but if you using 5.3+ closures are supported where callable arguments can be provided.</p>
    </div>
