    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$array</span>, <span class="hljs-string">'my_sort_function'</span>);

<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">var_dump</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$array</span>);

<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">my_sort_function</span>(<span class="hljs-params"><span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span></span>)
</span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;name &lt; <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;name;
}
</code></pre>
<p>The same code will be with the <code>count</code> field.</p>
<p>More details about <code>usort</code>: <a href="https://www.php.net/usort" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://www.php.net/usort</a></p>
<p>Btw, where did you get that array from? I hope that not from database?</p>
    </div>
