<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="17489368">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>If you need local based string comparison, you can use <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/function.strcoll.php" rel="nofollow"><code>strcoll</code></a> instead of <code>strcmp</code>.</p>

<p>Remeber to first use <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/function.setlocale.php" rel="nofollow"><code>setlocale</code></a> with <code>LC_COLLATE</code> to set locale information if needed.</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php">  <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$your_data</span>,function(<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>,<span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>){
    <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">setlocale</span> (LC_COLLATE, <span class="hljs-string">'pl_PL.UTF-8'</span>); <span class="hljs-comment">// Example of Polish language collation</span>
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">strcoll</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;name,<span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;name);
  });
</code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="mt24">
