<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="51105861">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>A simple alternative that allows you to determine dynamically the field on which the sorting is based:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-variable">$order_by</span> = <span class="hljs-string">'name'</span>;
<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$your_data</span>, function (<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>) <span class="hljs-keyword">use</span> ($<span class="hljs-title">order_by</span>)
{
    <span class="hljs-title">return</span> <span class="hljs-title">strcmp</span>($<span class="hljs-title">a</span>-&gt;{$<span class="hljs-title">order_by</span>}, $<span class="hljs-title">b</span>-&gt;{$<span class="hljs-title">order_by</span>});
});
</code></pre>

<p>This is based on the <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/class.closure.php" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Closure class</a>, which allows anonymous functions. It is available since PHP 5.3.</p>
    </div>
