    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>For my part, here is how I proceeded to sort an array of objects by object fields:</p>
<p>Code: (<a href="https://3v4l.org/7NiNb" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Demo</a>) -- sorts by last_name ASC, then first_name ASC</p>
<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-meta">&lt;?php</span>

<span class="hljs-variable">$array</span> = <span class="hljs-keyword">array</span>(
    (<span class="hljs-keyword">object</span>)<span class="hljs-keyword">array</span>(
        <span class="hljs-string">'first_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Léa'</span>,
        <span class="hljs-string">'last_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Weber'</span>,
    ),
    (<span class="hljs-keyword">object</span>)<span class="hljs-keyword">array</span>(
        <span class="hljs-string">'first_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Alexandre'</span>,
        <span class="hljs-string">'last_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Dupont'</span>,
    ),
    (<span class="hljs-keyword">object</span>)<span class="hljs-keyword">array</span>(
        <span class="hljs-string">'first_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Léa'</span>,
        <span class="hljs-string">'last_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Zotal'</span>,
    ),
    (<span class="hljs-keyword">object</span>)<span class="hljs-keyword">array</span>(
        <span class="hljs-string">'first_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Jérémie'</span>,
        <span class="hljs-string">'last_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Hoffmann'</span>,
    )
);

<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$array</span>, function(<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>) {
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> [<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;last_name, <span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;first_name]
           &lt;=&gt;
           [<span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;last_name, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;first_name];
});


<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">var_export</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$array</span>);
</code></pre>
<p>Outpout:</p>
<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-keyword">array</span> (
  <span class="hljs-number">0</span> =&gt; 
  (<span class="hljs-keyword">object</span>) <span class="hljs-keyword">array</span>(
     <span class="hljs-string">'first_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Alexandre'</span>,
     <span class="hljs-string">'last_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Dupont'</span>,
  ),
  <span class="hljs-number">1</span> =&gt; 
  (<span class="hljs-keyword">object</span>) <span class="hljs-keyword">array</span>(
     <span class="hljs-string">'first_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Jérémie'</span>,
     <span class="hljs-string">'last_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Hoffmann'</span>,
  ),
  <span class="hljs-number">2</span> =&gt; 
  (<span class="hljs-keyword">object</span>) <span class="hljs-keyword">array</span>(
     <span class="hljs-string">'first_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Léa'</span>,
     <span class="hljs-string">'last_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Weber'</span>,
  ),
  <span class="hljs-number">3</span> =&gt; 
  (<span class="hljs-keyword">object</span>) <span class="hljs-keyword">array</span>(
     <span class="hljs-string">'first_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Léa'</span>,
     <span class="hljs-string">'last_name'</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-string">'Zotal'</span>,
  ),
)
</code></pre>
<p>Arrow syntax with PHP7.4 and higher.
Makes sorting by multiple columns SUPER easy with the spaceship operator (&lt;=&gt;) aka the "Combined Comparison Operator" or "Three-way Comparison Operator".</p>
<p>Resource: <a href="https://wiki.php.net/rfc/combined-comparison-operator" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://wiki.php.net/rfc/combined-comparison-operator</a>
<a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/54647220/18090932">https://stackoverflow.com/a/54647220/18090932</a></p>
